DAMATURU – As part of recovery and resettlement efforts, the Yobe State government has revealed that it is set to recruit 3,000 new teachers for primary and secondary schools in the state. Commissioner of Home Affairs, Information and Culture, Abdullahi Bego, revealed on Thursday during the end of the year press conference held at Cedars Event Centre, Damaturu, the state capital. According to him, the decision was taken in recognition of the increasing students enrollment and educational transformation drive of Governor Mai Mala Buni. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The Commissioner also said that there’s a giant effort by the state government to reform the Almajiri system in the state. Speaking on the state of emergency in the education sector, he revealed that it began with the “First education summit, construction of more schools and classrooms and renovation of existing ones in 17 LGAs. FCT Minister Commends Police Officers For Securing Abuja Nigerians Must Look Forward To Prosperous 2021 – Makinde “It also includes the fencing of five model primary schools in five LGAs, construction of eight blocks of 38 classrooms,12 offices, 18 toilets, four flat blocks (24 classrooms, six toilets, six offices). “It also includes 69 indigenes sponsored to Law School, 204 Yobe youths sponsored for undergraduate courses to India And Asian countries (to leave within the new year if situation permits)”. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION